snippet.textDisplay: You help more people then you realise.., you help us (online fans from every stretch of the earth) every single day, and to get to my point; you helped put a smile on my face through the times where it seemed impossible; when I lost my daughter  in 2018 to SIDS. I was only 18 myself and I found your channel and I’ve been a dedicated fan ever since. I just want to say a tremendous thank you for helping me through the most trying time of my life without even knowing it. Now I’m 20 with a little 8 month old, beautiful baby boy; and I could not be any more proud to be a ladbaby/ladbaby and sons fan. Screw anyone that can’t understand that what you’re doing is 110% for charity, and to feed to hungry; to help families and those who struggle daily. Surely between us all, we can create enough “online roar” to get this Chris Moyles noticed for his distasteful behaviour towards this beautiful family. So much love from Australia- thank you for releasing this great song and for everything that you do! Xx

snippet.textDisplay:
Had to use a food bank because of our council house needing work. They couldn't find us a suitable house to live in while they were working on our house. They ended up letting us stay at a friend's house. But still charged us rent. We had to pay to heat two places etc etc. We had nothing. The council didn't care. Social work had to step in to help because they wanted to put us somewhere unsafe. My friend dragged me to the gp thinking I might get sectioned. We were just really lucky our friends support worker got involved to help us all get the food bank and a few quid on his Lecky meter to keep us going.
You're doing something amazing keep going! Honestly it's worth every minute.
